Master Node Network Configuration (Debian)

    Use the dhclient command on the interface end1 to obtain a dynamic IP address via DHCP.

    Check the assigned IP address and gateway using nmcli dev show end1.

    Identify the network connection name using the nmcli connection show command. The name is usually something like "Wired connection 2".

    Set a static IP address by modifying the connection using nmcli. Specify the IP address you got from DHCP, the subnet mask (in CIDR format, usually /24), and the gateway address. Also set the IP method to manual.

    Apply the new settings by bringing the connection down and then back up again using nmcli connection down and nmcli connection up.

    Confirm that the IP address has been set statically by verifying it with ip addr show.
